The FSEQNO variable in the ADJ form has a special interpretation compared to other forms.
For example, ADJ FSEQNO of '1' can be thought of as being '001', FSEQNO of '2' can be thought of as
being '002', and FSEQNO of '3' can be thought of as being '003'.
The first digit of FSEQNO relates to the corresponding ENF sequence number at that visit and the third
digit relates to the specific adjudicator who completed the adjudication form.

ElementDescription: Actual number of months from Baseline
Dental Status: Current problem with teeth and/or dentures at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= No Distress; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Severe; 999= N/A

ElementDescription: Dental Status: Dentures worn at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= Absent (No evidence of awareness of restlessness.; movements without inner restlessness as pseudoakathisia); 1= Questionable (Non-specific inner tension and fidgety movements); 2= Mild Akathisia (Awareness of restlessness in the inner/legs, worse when required to stand still, movements of akathisia not necessarily observed, causing little or no distress); 3= Moderate Akathisia (Same as mild akathisia above like rocking from foot to foot when standing, condition distressing); 4= Marked Akathisia (Compulsive desire to walk or pace, able to remain seated for at least five minutes, condition is distressing); 5= Severe Akathisia (Strong compulsion to pace up and down most of the time, unable to sit or lie down for more than a few minutes, intense distress and insomnia); 999= N/A

0= Normal; occasional fidgeting of limbs; 1= Presence of characteristics restless movements less than half the time; 2=Presence of characteristics restless movements present for at least half the observation period; 3= Engaged in characteristic restless movement, unable to remain seated or standing without walking or pacing; 999= N/A

ElementDescription: Subjective Awareness of Restlessness at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= Absence of inner restlessness; 1= Non-specific sense of inner restlessness; 2= Aware of leg restlessness or urge to move, worse when standing still; 3= Strong urge to move or pace most of the time; 999= N/A

ElementDescription: Subjective Distress related to Restlessness at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= No Distress; 1= Mild; 2= Moderate; 3= Severe; 999= N/A

0= Absent (No evidence of awareness of restlessness, inner restlessness as pseudoakathisia); 1= Questionable (Non-specific inner tension and fidgety movements); 2= Mild Akathisia (Awareness of restlessness in the legs and/or inner restlessness , worse when still; minor/no distress); 3= Moderate Akathisia (Awareness of restlessness and characteristics movements such as rocking from foot to foot when standing, condition distressing); 4= Marked Akathisia (Experiences restlessness including compulsive desire to walk or pace, able to remain seated for at least five minutes, condition is distressing); 5= Severe Akathisia (Reports a strong compulsion to pace up and down most of the time, unable to sit or lie down for more than a few minutes, intense distress/insomnia); 999= N/A

ElementDescription: Global Judgement: Severity of abnormal movements overall at timepoint_label
Global Judgement: Incapacitation due to abnormal movements at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= Normal, occasional fidgety movements of the limbs; 1= Presence of restless movements like shuffling or tramping movements of the legs/feet etc. but present for less than half the time; 2= Presence of restless movements like (1) above but present for at least half time; 3= Constant  restless movement, unable to remain seated or standing without walking or pacing; 999= N/A

ElementDescription: Global Judgement: Patient's awareness of abnormal movements at timepoint_label
Notes: 0= Absence of inner restlessness; 1= Non-specific sense of inner restlessness; 2= The patient is aware of an inability to keep the legs still, or a desire to move the legs, and/or complains of inner restlessness aggravated specifically by being required to stand still; 3= Awareness of an intense compulsion to move most of the time and/or reports a strong desire to walk or pace most of the time; 999= N/A
